snippet.textDisplay: I know they originally had more episodes planned for the season but this isn’t a bad place to leave off. Richard put Catherine in her place. Amelia and baby are both alive and well, Deluca proved that he is both brilliant and troubled (I’m really loving his performance! He looks so lost and childlike in this scene) and I know the fangirls/shippers are losing their minds right now because Mer believed in his diagnosis and is trying to take care of him, but I still don’t see anything but respect as a colleague, and concern for someone she loves in crisis. I also saw her asking Mcwidow to ask her again, which means she wasn’t making excuses. She really wants that drink with him. So the jury is still out on that one. Just please not another triangle! Glad Owen called off the wedding. Honestly up to this point I hadn’t really felt bad for him, but thinking about how she named their daughter after her lesbian lover and then this is how he finds out....on his wedding day...this just feels cruel even for him.
snippet.textOriginal: I know they originally had more episodes planned for the season but this isn’t a bad place to leave off. Richard put Catherine in her place. Amelia and baby are both alive and well, Deluca proved that he is both brilliant *and* troubled (I’m really loving his performance! He looks so lost and childlike in this scene) and I know the fangirls/shippers are losing their minds right now because Mer believed in his diagnosis and is trying to take care of him, but I still don’t see anything but respect as a colleague, and concern for someone she loves in crisis. I also saw her asking Mcwidow to ask her again, which means she wasn’t making excuses. She really wants that drink with him. So the jury is still out on that one. Just please not another triangle! Glad Owen called off the wedding. Honestly up to this point I hadn’t really felt bad for him, but thinking about how she named their daughter after her lesbian lover and then *this* is how he finds out....on his wedding day...this just feels cruel even for him.

snippet.textDisplay: it seems that they are building the character of the deluca in a way that he is gradually reaching the level of meredith. I mean, he is very handsome, he likes children, he supports her every moment but something was still missing. This disease, in addition to being extremely important and representative, will bring more maturity to the character with the experience of real pain.
